---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import FAQSection from '../components/FAQSection.astro';

const faqItems = [
  {
    question: 'Does Battery Calculators use cookies?',
    answer: 'No. We do not set any tracking cookies, advertising cookies, or analytics cookies on your device. The site uses only browser local storage for theme preference.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What data is stored in local storage?',
    answer: 'We use local storage for two purposes only: (1) remembering your dark/light theme preference, and (2) storing anonymous calculator feedback responses. This data never leaves your browser.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Will you add advertising cookies in the future?',
    answer: 'If we introduce advertising or analytics cookies in the future, this policy will be updated to disclose them. Any changes will be clearly documented on this page.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How can I clear my local storage data?',
    answer: 'You can clear local storage through your browser settings. This will reset your theme preference and clear any saved feedback responses.',
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy | Battery Calculators"
  description="Cookie policy for Battery Calculators. We do not use tracking cookies. Read about our minimal local storage usage."
  canonical="https://batterycalculators.com/cookies"
  schema="faqPage"
  schemaName="Battery Calculators Cookie Policy"
  schemaDescription="Cookie policy for Battery Calculators."
  schemaUrl="https://batterycalculators.com/cookies"
  faqItems={faqItems}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Cookie Policy' }]} />

    <div class="mb-12 border-b border-hairline pb-8">
      <span class="text-label-uppercase text-m-blue-light text-xs block mb-4">LEGAL COOKIES</span>
      <h1 class="text-display-md text-primary mb-6">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-body-md text-body font-light">
        Effective date: June 9, 2026.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-body-md text-body font-light">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">1. What Cookies Are</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that websites store on your device to remember preferences and track usage. Battery Calculators does not use any cookies of any kind.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">2. Analytics Usage</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          The site may use privacy-focused analytics (such as Google Analytics 4 or Microsoft Clarity) that are gated behind environment variables. These services may set cookies when enabled by the site operator.
        </p>
        <p>
          In the current deployment, analytics is not active and no analytics cookies are set. If analytics are enabled in the future, this policy will be updated accordingly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">3. Local Storage Usage</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          We use browser local storage (not cookies) for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-body-sm text-muted mb-4">
          <li><strong class="text-primary">Theme persistence:</strong> Stores your preferred color theme (dark or light mode) under the key <code class="text-m-blue-light">beh-theme</code>. This prevents a flash of wrong theme on page load.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-primary">Calculator feedback:</strong> Stores anonymous yes/no feedback responses for each calculator under keys like <code class="text-m-blue-light">feedback_calculator-name</code>. This prevents duplicate submissions and is never transmitted to a server.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All local storage data remains exclusively on your device. No local storage data is ever transmitted to any server, third-party service, or analytics platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">4. Future Advertising Cookies</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          If Battery Calculators introduces advertising cookies in the future — for example, through Google AdSense or other ad networks — this Cookie Policy will be updated to disclose:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-body-sm text-muted">
          <li>Which cookies are set and their purposes.</li>
          <li>Which third-party services are involved.</li>
          <li>How you can manage or opt out of advertising cookies.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">5. Managing Cookies</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Since we do not set cookies, there is nothing to manage on this site. However, you can control local storage through your browser settings:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 flex flex-col gap-2 text-body-sm text-muted">
          <li><strong class="text-primary">Clear local storage:</strong> Use your browser's developer tools or settings to clear site data. This will reset your theme preference and clear saved feedback responses.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-primary">Block local storage:</strong> Most browsers allow you to block local storage for specific sites, though this may affect theme functionality.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-8">
        <h2 class="text-title-lg text-primary uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">6. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about this Cookie Policy, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@batterycalculators.com" class="text-primary hover:text-m-blue-light transition-colors underline underline-offset-4">contact@batterycalculators.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <FAQSection items={faqItems} />
  </div>
</Layout>
